    <p>Fun Facts about Basket Weaving:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>1. Basket weaving is over 10,000 years old, making it one of humanity’s oldest crafts, even predating pottery.</li>
        <li>2. Weavers use locally available materials like willow, reeds, grasses, and bamboo, varying by region and culture.</li>
        <li>3. While baskets were originally made for carrying, storing, and fishing, many cultures now use them as intricate art pieces with symbolic designs.</li>
        <li>4. Basket Weaving is so important that even BYU has an article about the Basket Weaving class.</li>
    </ul>